<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-336-202  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 336 202.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer  June 1989 v22 n6 p91(7).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>A vision system for robotic inspection and manipulation.andO;(technical)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Trivedi, Mohan M.; Chen, ChuXin; Marapane, Suresh B.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A model-based computer vision system capable of autonomous roboticinspection and manipulation is described.andP;  The primary goal of arobot vision system is the accurate interpretation of a scene,using camera-captured images as the main input source.andP;  The systemanalyzes gray-scale images by working from models associated withexpected objects.andP;  These models are recorded in the system'sknowledge base.andP;  A set of general-purpose procedures lets the userencode model information.andP;  Other general-purpose proceduresacquire and segment images; extract specific features from theinput and match them with object attributes; and calibrate thecamera to determine three-dimensional locations of objects in thefield of view.andP;  Special-purpose procedures include routines forperformance verification, and determining the status of objectsrecognized by the general-purpose procedures.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     RobotsComputer VisionImage ProcessingSensorsModelsIntelligent Devices.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotographcharttable.andO;Caption:   Functional modules used to recognize objects and determine theirlocations. (chart)Objects on the test panel and their status information. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>